WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Hey there, Web Explorers!

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.800
We're looking at where to put JavaScript in your HTML.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:09.860
By the end of this video, you'll know exactly where to place your scripts for maximum efficiency

00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:10.860
and flexibility.

00:00:10.860 --> 00:00:14.000
Let's get coding!

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:15.700
First things first.

00:00:15.700 --> 00:00:17.820
JavaScript lives between script tags.

00:00:17.820 --> 00:00:19.220
That's like it's home.

00:00:19.220 --> 00:00:21.200
Let's start with an example.

00:00:21.200 --> 00:00:26.440
This simple script grabs an element with the ID of demo and changes its content.

00:00:26.440 --> 00:00:31.600
All examples might include type equals text slash javascript, but you don't need that

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:32.600
anymore.

00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:35.220
It's like wearing socks with sandals.

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:38.000
Just don't.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:39.700
So where should you place your scripts?

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:43.480
You can put them in the head or body or even both.

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:46.760
Let's take a look at head.

00:00:46.760 --> 00:00:50.560
This works, but scripts in the head run before the page content loads.

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:53.800
This might slow the rest of the page down.

00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:57.800
Let's try body.

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:03.040
When the script's in the body, it runs as the page loads, making things snappier for

00:01:03.040 --> 00:01:05.920
users.

00:01:05.920 --> 00:01:08.440
Want to take things to the next level?

00:01:08.440 --> 00:01:10.080
External JavaScript is where it's at.

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:14.400
It's like having a toolbox you can reuse on every page.

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:21.040
Using external scripts keeps your code neat, reusable, and faster thanks to browser caching.

00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:23.800
You can reference external scripts in different ways.

00:01:23.800 --> 00:01:27.680
Full URLs, relative paths, or no path at all.

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:29.720
The choice depends on your setup.

00:01:29.720 --> 00:01:35.520
Just remember, no script tags in your JavaScript files.

00:01:35.520 --> 00:01:36.960
So there you have it.

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:40.080
Scripts in the head or body, inline or external.

00:01:40.080 --> 00:01:43.680
It's all about what works for your project.

00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:45.080
Thanks for watching.

00:01:45.080 --> 00:01:48.160
Like and subscribe to get notified about our latest videos.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:53.600
For more coding tips and tricks, keep it locked right here on w3schools.com.

00:01:53.600 --> 00:01:56.680
Don't forget to try out what you've learned in our interactive editor.

00:01:56.680 --> 00:01:57.480
Happy coding!
